-- Shares in Banco Popolare rise 6 pct as launches cap hike
-- 
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 03:13AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, March 31 (Reuters) - Shares in Banco Popolare <BAPO.MI> rose 6 percent in early trade on Monday, the first day of a 1.5 billion euro ($2.06 billion)capital increase which according to the Italian press has attracted interest from international investors.

Italian newspaper Corriere della Sera quoted the cooperative bank's chief executive as saying on Sunday that purchases by U.S. investors were the reason for a 7 percent rise in the stock price on Friday. The shares retraced some of their gains to be quoted 4.5 percent higher at 0807 GMT, changing hands for 14.2 euros, against a 0.5 percent rise in Italy's all-share index <.FTITLMS>.